  "text": "Prolonged fasting in rats is characterized by insulin deficiency and insulin resistance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Both peripheral and hepatic insulin resistance to glucose metabolism have been observed in vivo [CITATION_3] . However, the insulin resistance of fasted animals, characterized by a reduced glucose disappearance rate during ITT, associated with reduced glycogen content in muscle and high levels of free fatty acids, may be downstream of IRSs/PI(3)K/AKT/GSK in muscle.",
